# Definition of Done

⚠️ **A task is ONLY considered complete when ALL of these are true:**
1. Code changes work as expected
2. Tests pass
3. ALL documentation is updated:
   - ✓ @000-variables.mdc[changelog] updated with current system date (not manually entered)
   - ✓ @000-variables.mdc[implementation_steps] status updated
   - ✓ @000-variables.mdc[current_state] reflects changes
   - ✓ @000-variables.mdc[backlog] updated

# Implementation Tracking Guidelines

## Task Implementation Process

```
┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐ │     │  IMPLEMENT      │     │  DOCUMENT       │
│     │  --------       │     │  --------       │
│ 1. Bugs first   │────▶│ 1. Edit files   │────▶│ 1. Update status│
│ 2. In-progress  │     │ 2. Run tests    │     │ 2. Track issues │
│ 3. High priority│     │ 3. Fix issues   │     │ 3. List changes │
└─────────────────┘     └───────────────────────┘
```

1. **Select task according to the priority order:**
   - Critical bugs (BUG-XXX) from @000-variables.mdc[backlog]
   - In-progress items from @000-variables.mdc[changelog]
   - Tasks with "Has Issues" status in @000-variables.mdc[implementation_steps]
   - High priority features from @000-variables.mdc[backlog]
   - Regular tasks from @000-variables.mdc[implementation_steps]

2. **Update @000-variables.mdc[changelog]:**
   - Move task from backlog to "In Progress"
   - Add start date and initial implementation notes
   - List files **with full paths** you plan to modify

3. **During implementation:**
   - Document issues encountered and solutions in backlck all modified files with explanations of what was changed and why
   - Document test results as you go

4. **Upon completion:**
   - Move task to "Completed Today" in @000-variables.mdc[changelog]
   - Update status in @000-variables.mdc[backlog]
   - Update corresponding task in @000-variables.mdc[implementation_steps]
   - Update relevant sections in @000-variables.mdc[current_state]
   - Create new backlog items for any discovered issues

## ID Tracking System

Use consistent IDs across all documents:
- **BUG-XXX**: For bugs (e.g., BUG-001)
- **FEAT-XXX**: For features (e.g., FEAT-001)
- **IMP-XXX**: For improvements (e.g., IMP-001)
- **TECH-XXX**: For technical debt (e.g., TECH-001)

Guidelines for ID usage:
- IDs are permanent and travel with the item through all documents
- Never reuse IDs, even if items are deleted
- Always use the full ID format when referencing items
- For subtasks, use hierarchical format: FEAT-001.1, FEAT-001.2, etc.

## Status Tracking Format

###.mdc[backlog]

```markdown
### [ID]: [Title]
- **Status**: [Complete/In Progressarted]
- **Testing**: [Passed/Failed/Not Started]
- **Dependencies**: [List of IDs, e.g., FEAT-003, BUG-002]
- **Added**: YYYY-MM-DD
- **Description**: [Detailed description]

#### Implementation Notes
- ****: 
  - [Issue]: [Solution]

- **Files Modified**:
  - `path/to/file`: [What changed and why]

- **Testing Results**:
  - [Test]: [Result]
```

### In @000-variables.mdc[changelog]

```markdown
### [ID]: [Title]
- **Started**: YYYY-MM-DD
- **Completed**: YYYY-MM-DD (for completed items)
- **Implementation Notes**: [Details]
- **Files Modified**: [List with explanations]
- **Testing Results**: [Summary]
```

### In @000-variables.mdc[implementation_steps]

```markdown
### [Task Number] [Task Name] (ID: [ID])
- **Status**: [Complete/In Progress/Has Issues/Not Started]
- **Testing**: [Passed/Failed/Not Started]
  - [Test Name]: [Passed/Failed]
- **Dependencies**: [Task references or "None"]
- **Last Updated**: [Date]
```

## Status Definitions

- **Complete**: All requirements implemented and tested
- **In Progress**: Implementation has started but is not finished
- **Has Issues**: Implementation attempted but has known problems
- **Not Started**: Implementation has not begun

## Testing Status Definitions

- **Passed**: All tests passing
- **Failed**: One or more tests failing
- **Not Started**: Testing has not begun

## Documentation Synchronization

When updating task status, ensure all documents are synchronized:
1. Update the item in @000-variables.mdc[backlog]
2. Update the item in @000-variables.mdc[changelog]
3. Update corresponding task in @000-variables.mdc[implementation_steps]
4. Update relevant sections in @000-variables.mdc[current_state]

## Rule Application

This rule should be applied whenever:
1. Starting a new development session
2. Selecting a task to work on
3. During implementation
4. Completing a task
5. Encountering implementation issues
6. Planning next development steps